Wash and dry produce.

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry; season with @bold & savory steak spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot #large pan{}. Add steak; cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

> TIP: Move on to Step 2 while the steak cooks!

While steak cooks, trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{2} and thinly slice leaves. Thinly slice @mini cucumber{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix @Greek vinaigrette{3%ounce} with @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} if desired. In a #large bowl{}, toss lettuce, cucumber, tomatoes, and @feta cheese{1/2%cup} with as much dressing as you like.

Wrap @pita bread{2} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}. Cut into quarters.

Slice steak against the grain.

Top salad with steak and serve with pitas on the side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.